  "prompt": "Why isn't WhatsApp fixing the \"copy multiple messages includes date and time stamp along with it\" bug?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why WhatsApp hasn't yet addressed the issue where copying multiple messages includes date and time stamps:\n\n1. **Priority and Resources**: WhatsApp might be prioritizing other features or fixes that are deemed more urgent or important by their team. They have to allocate their resources to what's considered most critical for usability, security, or user demand.\n\n2. **Technical Complexity**: The problem might be more technically complex than it appears. Fixing it could require changes to the app's underlying architecture or message handling systems, which might take longer to implement and test.\n\n3. **Impact Analysis**: WhatsApp might be conducting a broader impact analysis to ensure that fixing this bug doesn't inadvertently cause other issues or affect other functionalities within the app.\n\n4. **Feedback and Demand**: If this issue hasn't been reported widely by users or isn't seen as significantly impacting the overall user experience, it might be deemed a lower priority. User feedback often drives which bugs are addressed sooner.\n\n5. **Scheduled Updates**: The fix might be planned for a future update. Large applications often batch multiple fixes and new features into scheduled releases rather than rolling out minor updates frequently.\n\n6. **Design Intent**: In some cases, what users perceive as a bug might actually be an intentional design choice. The inclusion of date and time stamps might be intended for clarity or context when copying messages.\n\nIt's always good practice to directly report such issues to the app\u2019s support or feedback section to ensure they're aware of it. This can help prioritize fixes in upcoming updates.",
